Boat Sinks in Brazil’s Capital; at Least 2 Dead, Others Missing

-- B y   C a r l a   S i m o e s
-- 
2011-05-23T19:35:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/boat-sinks-in-brazil-s-capital-at-least-2-dead-others-missing.html
A boat sank in Brasilia’s Paranoa
lake yesterday, killing at least two people and leaving seven or
eight others missing, according to an official at the fire
department.  Imaginatium, a private boat, sank at around 9:00 p.m.,
Firewoman Vanessa Signale, said in a telephone interview from
Brasilia. Ninety-three people, including crew, where rescued,
she said. A seven-month baby and a 22-year-old woman died. The
boat had capacity for 92 people including crew, according to an
emailed statement from the Navy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carla Simoes in Brasilia at 
 csimoes1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
